+- The negative classifications are decent but incomplete. They include solution-class mismatch, viscous-defect collapse, non-coercivity, nonlocal-strain freedom, and endpoint-transfer failure. Missing are at least two common failure modes: prior-art redundancy and proxy-bridge inflation. The chain can fail not because it is false but because it rederives known nonclosing strain criteria in new language.
